{"id":14881678,"mediaExerciseId":"f402a00f-c457-4b1d-baff-aa7cb28dfb40","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"19","chapterTitle":"Cash and Liquidity Management","groupId":612447,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":660,"solutions":[{"id":6005393,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we need to find the average daily float. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/d40651567d8a19dddc0d0ab7422e10d5/ae3c3dfb5514a4a5f68adce044b15264/lateximg_large.png","width":738},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/d40651567d8a19dddc0d0ab7422e10d5/ae3c3dfb5514a4a5f68adce044b15264/lateximg.png","width":369}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The average daily float is the product of average amount of checks received per day and the average number of days delay, divided by the number of days in a month. Assuming the month has a $30$ days, the average\ndaily float is \n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{Average daily float}&=\\frac{\\text{Total float}}{\\text{Total days}}\\\\\n&=\\frac{\\$113,000\\cdot 4}{30}\\\\\n&=\\frac{\\$452,000}{30}\\\\\n&=\\$15,066.67\n\\end{align*}$$\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"bacaca20-74e5-4f45-bf59-6837148b5d22","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":2}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corpora